[I] GTK+ DocBook Documentation Generator

[T] GTK-Doc is used to document C code. It is typically used to document
[T] the public API of libraries, such as the GTK+ and Gnome libraries.
[T] But it can also be used to document application code.

[U] https://www.gnome.org

[A] Damon Chaplin <damon@gnome.org>
[A] Owen Taylor <otaylor@redhat.com>

[M] Juergen "George" Sawinski <jsaw@gmx.net>
[M] Susanne Klaus <vadja@gmx.de>

[C] extra/tool extra/desktop/gnome
[F] CROSS

[E] add pygments libxml

[L] GPL
[V] 1.36.0
[P] X -----5---9 126.650

[CV-URL] https://download.gnome.org/sources/gtk-doc/cache.json
[D] a2feb54c6e8c488f7934997dc8f1fa470b3827d642ff1d2f3328d56e gtk-doc-1.36.0.tar.xz https://download.gnome.org/sources/gtk-doc/1.36/

. $base/package/*/*/gnome-conf.in
atstage cross && export XSLTPROC=/usr/bin/xsltproc XMLCATALOG=/usr/bin/xmlcatalog
